.th FREEZE VI 26-March-1980
.sh NAME
freeze \*- freeze GRINNELL video digitizer input
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd freeze
[nframes shift]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Freeze
is used to to stop input from the video digitizer, or to
enter a number of frames from the digitizer and then stop input.
.s3
The optional parameters
.it nframes
and
.it shift
specify how many frames to enter, and how much to shift each frame.
.it Nframes
is a decimal number from 1 to 255, and
.it shift
is a decimal number from 0 to 7.
